        [
          "You negotate luxury travel and entertainment for the elite among supernatural society. And you’re very, very good at it.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "LAB"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "The best way to hide a secret is to tell everyone about it. Most people think the Society of Crossed Keys is a fabrication of Wes Anderson. Not true. The Society of the Crossed Keys is very real, and is very good at what it does: negotiating luxury travel and entertainment for the elite among supernatural society. And you’re very, very good at it. Of all things, you began life in a circus: your father was a highwire walker, your mother a fortune teller. From there you learned about customer service - not that the customer is always right, but instead in how to manage expectations. All was well, until you started to hear the voices in your head. For the most part, they were benign and even helpful. But the darker ones, the ones that whispered behind your closed eyes, they were the ones you worried most about. They drove you to murder your father and cut the tongue of your mother so she couldn’t tell; they drove you to set the tents on fire. They told you you had done all that you could here and that more was waiting for you elsewhere. Which is how you found yourself under the wing of Rebecca Stone. She was able to help you negotiate with the voices, and all she needed in return was your mortal life. From there, she indoctrinated you into both kindred society as well as the Crossed Keys. Now you serve the wealthy and elite. You take a measure of pride from it, the way you imagine Jeeves or Alfred Pennyworth does. You accomplish that which is supposed to be impossible. Except the voices always are telling you could do more…."
        ],
